article.description: Jeff Dowtin had 24 points as Rhode Island beat Richmond 78-67 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Dowtin scores 24 to carry Rhode Island past Richmond 78-67
article.linkText: Dowtin scores 24 to carry Rhode Island past Richmond 78-67
article.story: RICHMOND, Va. -- Jeff Dowtin had 24 points as Rhode Island beat Richmond 78-67 on Wednesday night. Fatts Russell had 19 points for Rhode Island (8-6, 1-1 Atlantic 10 Conference). Tyrese Martin added 10 points and seven rebounds. Cyril Langevine had seven rebounds. Jacob Gilyard had 19 points for the Spiders (6-9, 0-2). Grant Golden added 17 points, eight rebounds and six assists. Jake Wojcik had 12 points. Rhode Island matches up against George Mason (8-7, 2-0) at home on Sunday. Richmond faces George Washington (5-10, 1-1) on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
